---
import Page from '@layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of service and conditions of use for API Hub."
>
  <div style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-3); margin: 0 0 2rem;">
      Last updated: March 2026
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      1. Scope
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      These Terms of Service govern the use of the website API Hub (hereinafter "Website"),
      operated by Belkis Aslani, Vogelsangstr. 32, 71691 Freiberg am Neckar, Germany.
      By accessing the Website, you accept these terms.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      2. Description of Service
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      API Hub is a free, non-commercial directory of publicly available APIs.
      The Website serves solely to visualize and improve the searchability of data from the open-source project
      <a href="https://github.com/public-apis/public-apis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">public-apis/public-apis</a>.
      We do not offer or broker any API services ourselves.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      3. Usage Rights
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      Use of the Website is free of charge. The source code of the Website is available under the MIT License
      on <a href="https://github.com/BEKO2210/API_directory" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">GitHub</a>.
      The API data is subject to the license of the
      <a href="https://github.com/public-apis/public-apis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">original repository</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      4. Disclaimer
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      The information provided on this Website is offered without any warranty regarding accuracy,
      completeness, or timeliness. The listed APIs are operated by third parties. We assume no liability
      for the availability, security, or functionality of the listed API services. Use of the listed APIs
      is at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      5. External Links
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      This Website contains links to external websites. The operators of the linked pages are solely
      responsible for their content and data practices. No illegal content was identifiable at the time
      of linking.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      6. Availability
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      We strive to provide uninterrupted availability of the Website. However, there is no entitlement to
      permanent availability. Maintenance or technical issues may lead to temporary unavailability.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      7. Changes to Terms
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
      We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. The current version is always available
      on this page. Continued use of the Website after a change constitutes acceptance of the
      modified terms.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">
      8. Governing Law
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
      The laws of the Federal Republic of Germany shall apply. The place of jurisdiction is, to the
      extent permitted by law, Freiberg am Neckar, Germany.
    </p>
  </div>
</Page>
